Floating Record™ Vertical Turntable




Chicago, IL

Product Design






$1,575,976


pledged of $50,000 goal




4,218


backers











The Floating Record is a high-performance turntable that plays your records vertically through built-in, dynamic, full-range stereo speakers (or via RCA line out). We reimagined turntable technology that uses audiophile-grade materials and components. The result is a visually and mechanically sound way to experience vinyl music.


Floating Record Vertical Turntable Prototype




















Floating Record Maple Prototype


At Gramovox our design philosophy is to reimagine vintage audio design with modern technology. In this spirit, we sought to reimagine the record player. We yearned for a visceral vinyl experience that showcased the record as both art and a medium to produce analog sound. The result is a high-performance turntable that plays your records vertically—producing the illusion that it’s floating.


Floating Record Walnut Prototype




We designed the Floating Record for everyone from the first-time record listener 
to the seasoned vinyl enthusiast. You’ll be spinning tunes out of the box in a matter
 of minutes. You don't need to set up your cartridge or purchase additional outboard
 gear such as phono pre-amps, amplifiers and speakers (although you have the option to).
 All of these are included in our integrated design.








Floating Record Walnut Prototype


Don’t hide your vinyl. Show it off. The Floating Record allows you to showcase your vinyl while maintaining high-quality playback. 








Floating Record Maple Prototype


Traditional record players take up a lot of space and require additional 
components such as pre-amps, amps, integrated receivers, speakers and 
all the necessary cables. However, the Floating Record’s integrated design allows it to beautifully fit into most environments with ease.


Floating Record Walnut Prototype





Floating Record Maple Prototype









We’ve engineered the Floating Record to flawlessly play your vinyl vertically and output full-range stereo sound. We deconstructed the elements of a premium turntable setup and reconstructed them in a manner that maintains their high-performance standards. 


Floating Record MDF w/ Walnut Veneer (Production Version)





Floating Record MDF w/ Walnut Veneer (Production Version)





Floating Record MDF w/ Walnut Veneer (Production Version)















Listen in 33 ⅓ or 45 RPM


You can easily switch between 33 ⅓ or 45 RPM by moving the silicon belt over the inner or outer groove of the middle gear. We include record clamps for both types of records.







Floating Record MDF w/ Walnut Veneer (Production Version)


You can bypass the integrated speakers and use the Floating Record as a standalone Hi-Fi turntable for your own audio setup. 


RCA Line Out to External Speakers


You have the option of bypassing the internal amp and speakers and outputting an RIAA equalized line level signal from the built in phono-preamp via the "Line Out" RCA jacks. The switch is used to choose between Onboard and Line Out. The Onboard position activates the built-in phono stage--the 15 watt digital power amp and built-in speakers. The “Line Out” bypasses the internal amplifier and speakers, and takes the signal from our built-in phono-preamp to the “Line Out” RCA jacks. This allows the player to be used as a standalone Hi-Fi turntable. RCA out is a line level signal that is used to connect to an existing stereo system via the “Tape in” or “Aux In” inputs on your receiver, pre-amp or amp.


Floating Record Maple Prototype










Floating Record MDF w/ Walnut Veneer (Production Version)


The Floating Record comes with a dynamic, full-range audio system. We use two Tymphany 2” neodymium speakers driven by a
 15w per channel digital amplifier. The speaker cavities incorporate 
tuned bottom porting to offer superior bass response. We achieved the best possible sound without compromising aesthetics or performance.










We created a fully-adjustable, carbon-fiber tone-arm. This audiophile staple is perfectly balanced radially around its main pivot bearing axis. This allows it to be played in a vertical position and not flop to one side or the other.The tracking force is (dynamically) applied by a spring as opposed to the usual counterweights found in horizontal record players in which the arm is (statically) balanced. Spring loaded tracking force is beneficial in regards to consistency of the force applied—especially on warped records. Our tone-arms are factory-set at the optimal tracking force of ~2 grams.










Since our tonearm is perfectly balanced radially around its main pivot bearing axis, it does not skew or favor one groove side over the other. Typically, the modulations in the groove can cause friction and this contributes to centripetal force acting on the arm and causing it to skate towards the center of the record. Our rigorous testing ensured no performance issues. 









The Audio Technica AT95E is a warm sounding cartridge with a smooth high end, sweet mids and rich low end. The dual magnet cartridge comes with an elliptical diamond stylus. An elliptical stylus has many advantages over spherical styli. The elliptical stylus has two radii, the front radius being wider than the side radius. This allows the stylus to ride in the center of the groove, like the conical stylus, while the smaller side radius can more accurately track higher frequencies.Compared to the conical stylus, however, the elliptical stylus has a longer vertical contact area and a narrower front to back contact area within the record groove. The elliptical tip follows the groove modulations with more precision, providing improved frequency response, improved phase response, and lower distortion, specifically in the inner grooves of the record. 







We've developed a robust cueing mechanism that allows you to effortlessly cue your records. This helps reduce the risk of scratching your records or damaging your stylus. Now you can cue up your favorite track with ease. How Does It Work?1. Set your tone-arm2. Push cue lever3. Watch your stylus gracefully fall onto the record







Belt-Driven Turntable on Walnut Prototype


The Floating Record uses a belt drive system with a silicone belt to help isolate motor vibrations from the platter. We choose a high quality A/C synchronous motor and custom-designed a high precision motor control circuit to ensure silent operation and consistent speed. This is mounted with rubber isolation bushings to help decouple it from the base. Our main platter spindle is made from stainless steel and runs in bronze bushing with a teflon bottom. The plinth is CNC-machined out of high mass acrylic to help reduce resonance. The platter is also CNC-machined acrylic to add mass and help reduce resonance. All this works together to help our turntable achieve smooth, consistent playback.








The Floating Record’s base will be composed of a miter-folded MDF box finished with a genuine Maple or Walnut veneer. This method maintains our desired aesthetic, prevents warping and minimizes the waste factor. The finished product will look beautiful, sound great and maintain a high level of performance. Our construction method adheres to industry-tested best practices. Overall, our bases produce a rich aesthetic that beautifully complements your home or office.










We’re using world-class wood, metal and electronics suppliers to produce parts that meet our high-tolerances. The most crucial part—the final assembly—is handled by highly-trained electro-mechanical assembly engineers in Chicago. Each unit is thoroughly tested before being packaged and shipped out.





Walnut or Maple Veneer Wood Base 
Fully-adjustable Carbon-Fiber Tone-Arm w/ dynamically set tracking force 
 AT95E Audio-Technica Dual Magnet Cartridge with Elliptical Diamond Stylus 
2” Neodymium Full-Range Stereo Speakers 
Built in phono stage with RIAA equalization curve 
Onboard 2x15W Stereo Audio Amplifier, Tripath TA2024 Class-D / Class-T architecture 
Manual Belt-Drive System (33 1/3 or 45 RPM) 
A/C Synchronous motor with super high precision motor control circuit 
Low resonance, high mass, acrylic Plinth and Platter 
RCA Line Out 
Headphone Jack 
Universal AC to DC power supply compatible with US standard 60 Hz, 110/120 VAC or European standard 50 Hz, 220/240 VAC (Snap-in power plugs are included for operation in countries around the world) 
17” Wide x 10” Deep x 16” Tall 
13 lbs. 
 Vibration Damping Feet










1. Floating Record (Walnut or Maple Wood Veneer Base) body2. Polished Acrylic Platter3. Felt Mat4. Silicon Belt5. Record Clamp (33 1/3 & 45 RPM)6. A/C Adapter (USA or International w/ adapter plug points)







Floating Record MDF w/ Walnut Veneer (Production Version)





Floating Record MDF w/ Maple Veneer (Production Version)












We will ship complete units from our fulfillment facility in Chicago, Illinois to anywhere around the world. All units will be shipped in a custom, reusable ~22"x14"x16" slotted carton with form-fitting high-density polyethylene foam for maximum protection. All orders will include UPS online parcel tracking and insurance.United States: $20. Package will be sent via UPS Ground for 1-5 day delivery once shipped.Canada: $55. Package will be sent via UPS Worldwide for 2-5 day delivery once shipped. Local taxes may apply. European Union: $95. Package will be pre-cleared into EU prior to UPS parcel delivery and includes duties/VAT pre-paid by Gramovox. All other destination countries will ship via UPS Worldwide. Additional duties/taxes may apply depending on your destination country.














With every Gramovox product, you receive our 1-year Limited Warranty. For more details, see the warranty section of our website.










Team Gramovox wouldn’t be here today if it weren’t for backers like you who kickstarted our first product and company in December 2013. You helped us bring the Bluetooth Gramophone to market, and we successfully delivered a superbly crafted work of functional art. Since then our team has rapidly grown. We’re made up of designers, audio engineers, craftsmen and operations experts. We’re a tight family with a mission to delight the world with products that reimagine vintage audio design with modern technology.




Risks and challenges
Since our first successful Kickstarter campaign, we’ve become experts in manufacturing, operations and logistics. Over the past year we’ve established solid relationships with the suppliers we’re using for the Floating Record. We’re all one team with a goal of producing the best quality product.
Learn about accountability on Kickstarter


